### [v0.4] - 2025-12-XX
#### Added
- Kernel::handleRateLimit() for handling global rate limit configuration and endpoint specific rate limit.
- HeaderSlave::writeRateLimitHeaders() for writing rate limit headers.
- Request::get() for getting sanitized or raw query data.
- Request::post() for getting sanitized or raw request data.
- SanitizeType enum for defining data sanitization levels.
- Request::getRemoteAddress() for getting remote address (unless is defined as hidden).
- AuthWorker::regenerateCSRF() for regenerating CSRF token.
- DataSlave optional SSL/TLS support via DB_SSL and DB_SSL_CA environment variables.
- FileWorker and FileSlave for managing file uploads.
- CacheWorker and CacheSlave for managing cache.
- Support for APCU, SHMOP and File cache.
- Config::configureCache(...) for defining file cache configuration.
- Cache garbage collector via CacheSlave::runGarbageCollector().
- Request::file() for getting uploaded files tmp path.
- Bee::getFileMimeType() for getting accurate file mime type.
- CDN Router for handling CDN routes.
- MiddlewareType enum for defining middleware types. (VIEWS, API, CDN or ROUTER)
- Response::file(...) for handling CDN endpoint responses.
- Config::configureRedirects(...) for defining path redirects.
- Config::configureRateLimit(...) for defining global rate limit configuration.
- Config::configureLengthLimit(...) for defining maximum input length and file upload size allowed.
- Config::getRateLimit() for getting global rate limit configuration depending of middleware.
- Endpoint::cdn() for handling CDN endpoints.
- Endpoint::router() for nesting router files inside the main router.
- Auto-trailing slashes for request and endpoint paths.
- Request::getType() for getting request type.
- Router::add(...) for adding endpoints and subrouters.

#### Changed
- DataSlave now uses regex filtering for injected strings (table, cols, conditions and orderBy).
- Request now sanitizes data in different levels of severity.
- MailSlave::getMailTemplate() now uses realpath() to prevent directory traversal attacks.
- MailSlave::setMailerAttachments() now uses realpath() to prevent directory traversal attacks.
- Type enums have been relocated to a new namespace.
- Skeleton has been updated to account for recent changes.
- Template component now allows for nested setters.
- DataType enum now supports 55 data types.
- Router factory now only specifies middleware type. 
- Router now uses O(1) hash map lookup for endpoint matching.
- Collection now stores values internally with key-based O(1) lookup.
- AuthSlave now calls session_start() only when needed, improving performance.
- DataSlave now supports persistent PDO connections for better performance.

#### Fixed
- Logs are not being stored inside storage directory.
- AuthWorker::autologin() produces a timing attack vulnerability.

#### Removed
- sitePath parameter from Server::getConfiguration(), Server::getTemplate(), Server::getViewRouter(), Server::getApiRouter() 
- getDataItem() method from Request component is getting deprecated.
- getOriginInfo() method from Request component.
- Permissions-Policy meta tag from main.php template.
- initializeServer() method from Server class.
- preload(...) method from Server class.
- isApi() method from Request component.
- configureSecurity(...) method from Config class.

---

### [v0.3] - 2025-12-17
#### Added
- Config::configurePrivacy(...) for defining whether to register logs or restrict what data to register.
- Collection and Item components for handling key-value pair arrays.
- ValidationWorker for validating data such as email addresses or passwords.
- ValidationFlags collection for handling validation flags.
- API Response success boolean field.
- AlreadyAuthorizedException for handling unauthorized exclusive endpoints.
- Endpoint argument unauthorizedExclusive for handling unauthorized exclusive endpoints.
- LogWorker::debug() for debugging system logs.
- MailWorker for sending crafted and dynamic emails.
- Mail component for crafting mail objects.
- Item::mail and Item::file for helping with Mail crafting.
- AUTH_DOMAIN env variable for defining global authorization domain.
- Config::configureSecurity(...) for defining security policies against DDoS attacks and input length. 
- DataWorker warnings against SQL injection.  

#### Changed
- Skeleton: Update build.sh to account for last changes.
- DataWorker now uses Collection and Item components.
- Router now uses Collection and Item components.
- Template now uses Collection and Item components.
- PHP Version downgrade to 8.4 to support hosting deployment.
- System logs now are collapsed so they take less space.
- LogWorker prefix for each type of log.
- Template component now sanitizes file paths.
- AuthSlave::validateCSRF() now uses hash_equals() for improved security.
- Improved PDO Exception handling in DataSlave.
- Jquery is now loaded from local files.
- HeaderSlave::addSecurityHeaders() now uses a more secure CSP.

#### Fixed
- Skeleton: Sites folder not accounted for deploy.sh and index.php
- Skeleton: .htaccess fallback not working.
- Skeleton: Sites folder not accounted for watch.sh
- NotFoundException and NotAuthorizedException are not being handled correctly.
- ValidationWorker is not initialized. (jesus christ)
- DataWorker::getOne() crashes when no result is found.
- AlreadyAuthorizedException is not being handled.
- Config::configureAuthorization(...) is not enabling global authorization correctly.
- CSRF token session is not being correctly injected into the main template.

#### Removed
- htmlspecialchars method from Request::sanitizeData().
- meta tag HTTP headers from main.php Template.
- API Response status string field.
- domain configuration from Config::configureAuthorization(...)

---

### [v0.2] - 2025-12-06
#### Added
- Configuration of path redirects for 404 error.
- Support for .html template injection before and after #main div.
- Server::preload(__DIR__) for loading environment configuration.
- Server::getConfiguration(), Server::getTemplate(), Server::getViewRouter(), Server::getApiRouter() for modular loading.
- Test suite added.
- Feature to enable authorization across parent domain and all subdomains.
- Bee::getBaseDomain() and Bee::getBuiltDomain(...) for getting base domain and subdomain.
- Bee::hashPassword(...) and AuthWorker::autologin(...) for automatic password hashing and auto-login.
- AuthWorker::getAuthorizedUserId() for getting authorized user ID.
- New methods and uses for SQL queries in DataWorker and DataSlave.
- Deploy script for Apache.

#### Changed
- Template::oneline() is now Template::flex(), allowing for dynamic creation of templates.
- Improvement of HTML semantics for main.php.
- Server component is now a unique class with unique traits. Is not a component anymore.
- Bee::env method now supports default value if environment variable is not found.
- Improved URI parsing and path normalization.
- Improved Exception handling for easier maintenance.
- Standarization of JS native libraries (Lib class) for increased compatibility.
- Request::getDataItem() method has been optimized for better performance.
- Skeleton site structure is now insite sites/ folder.

#### Fixed
- Unauthorized redirect path not working for views, throws 403.
- Default JS function request not sending json data correctly.
- getDataItem() crashes when parsing array or objects.
- Unauthorized sites not redirecting to configured subdomain.

#### Removed
- Config $allowedHosts parameter. Couldn't find a real security use for this feature.